content.text: Learn how to add Google Charts to your web page.
content.html: Learn how to add Google Charts to your web page.

content.text: Start with a simple basic web page.
content.html: Start with a simple basic web page.

content.text: Add a <div> element with the id "piechart":

content.code_html:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h1>My Web Page</h1>

<div id="piechart"></div>

</body>

syntax_highlighting.text: // Draw the chart and set the chart values

// Optional; add 
  a title and set the width and height of the chart

// Display the chart 
  inside the <div> element with id="piechart"

content.code_html:
<script type="text/javascript">
// Load google charts
google.charts.load('current', {'packages':['corechart']});
google.charts.setOnLoadCallback(drawChart);

// Draw the chart and set the chart values
function drawChart() {
  var data = google.visualization.arrayToDataTable([
  ['Task', 'Hours per Day'],
  ['Work', 8],
  ['Friends', 2],
  ['Eat', 2],
  ['TV', 2],
  ['Gym', 2],
  ['Sleep', 8]
]);

  // Optional; add a title and set the width and height of the chart
  var options = {'title':'My Average Day', 'width':550, 'height':400};

  // Display the chart inside the <div> element with id="piechart"
  var chart = new google.visualization.PieChart(document.getElementById('piechart'));
  chart.draw(data, options);
}
</script>
